### Key Findings

- **#282 Command Palette**: Use `cmdk` directly (not via shadcn CLI). Set `filter={null}` and call the backend vector search API with debounce — cmdk's built-in fuzzy scoring runs locally but the issue spec requires the existing vector search. Prefix routing (`>`, `#type`) is best done by conditionally rendering `CommandGroup`s, not through the filter function.

- **#283 Keyboard Shortcuts**: `react-hotkeys-hook` is the clear choice. Use `'meta+k, ctrl+k'` comma syntax for cross-platform support in a single call. All shortcuts should be registered in one top-level component. `preventDefault: true` is required for `meta+n` (otherwise opens new browser window).

- **#284 Calendar View**: `react-big-calendar` with `dateFnsLocalizer` — **date-fns is already in package.json**, so no new date-library dependency. Use `eventPropGetter` for type-based color coding and `onSelectEvent` to open the detail panel.

### Gaps

- Connecting cmdk to the backend vector search API requires custom implementation (no established pattern found) — debounced fetch + `filter={null}` is the approach.
- react-big-calendar's SASS-based styles may need CSS custom property overrides to integrate cleanly with Tailwind 4.

Sources:
- [shadcn/ui Command docs](https://ui.shadcn.com/docs/components/command)
- [cmdk GitHub](https://github.com/pacocoursey/cmdk)
- [react-hotkeys-hook docs](https://react-hotkeys-hook.vercel.app/docs/api/use-hotkeys)
- [react-big-calendar GitHub](https://github.com/jquense/react-big-calendar)
- [Builder.io React Calendar comparison](https://www.builder.io/blog/best-react-calendar-component-ai)
